.SH NAME
Selection.anchorOffset \- Selection: anchorOffset property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Selection.anchorOffset\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns the number of characters that the selection\(cqs anchor is
offset within the \f[CR]Selection.anchorNode\f[R] if said node is of
type \f[CR]Text\f[R], \f[CR]CDATASection\f[R] or \f[CR]Comment\f[R].
.PP
In the case of \f[CR]Selection.anchorNode\f[R] being another type of
node, \f[B]\f[CB]Selection.anchorOffset\f[B]\f[R] returns the number of
\f[CR]Node.childNodes\f[R] the selection\(cqs anchor is offset within
the \f[CR]Selection.anchorNode\f[R].
.PP
This number is zero\-based.
If the selection begins with the first character in the
\f[CR]Selection.anchorNode\f[R], \f[CR]0\f[R] is returned.
.SH VALUE
A number.
